The paper focuses on the problem of structural learning of Bayesian Networks, which is a common topic in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of Suppes-Bayes Causal Networks (SBCNs) to model cumulative phenomena suggests a potential connection to the subfield of social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the use of search techniques and regularization methods, which are common topics in the subfields of data mining (cs.DM) and information theory (cs.IT).
